i have a week old infant he will stay up for to hours at a time i have tried every thing i have tried rocking him which i put him down after he falls asleep only to awake seconds later screaming to playing soft music the letting him cry himself to sleep has yet to work i need advice is it possible he has insomnia i have had the same problem with my week old son the best thing that worked for me was trying to establish more of a routine at night letting him cry himself to sleep is not good at this age as they are too young he will think you arent responding to him and cant console himself yet at night i just try to make it dark and get him into a routine such as feeding him his bottle a bath winding him down also i learned how to swaddle him with a blanket which seemed to help as well good luck and this will help i hope Insomnia Sleep Social rule Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Breastfeeding Characters of The Sandman The Amber Spyglass Urinary incontinence Siegfried Schtauffen The Subtle Knife 2005 trial of Michael Jackson The Catcher in the Rye Sleep apnea Narcolepsy Nightmare (Soul Calibur) Saturday Night Live Sleep disorder The Inside Customs and etiquette of Japan The Life and Times of Juniper Lee The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Childbirth Phoebe Halliwell Caffeine The Apprentice 2 Macbeth Episodes of Lost (Season 2) Sleep debt Infant A Canticle for Leibowitz Shaggy dog story Seiken Densetsu 3 Sin City Sleep deprivation Sudden infant death syndrome Ayyavazhi mythology Cat Combat stress reaction WCBS-FM Delayed sleep phase syndrome Blankets (graphic novel) Odyssey Socrates Marching band About a Boy Co-sleeping Fight Club Scenes from a Memory Stroke Book of Isaiah Odysseus The Dunciad The Star Wars Holiday Special Miss Saigon Garfield Pitaten Carpal tunnel syndrome Norwegian Wood (This Bird Has Flown) Characters in the Smurfs Futurama (TV series - season 5) Saki Sant Thakar Singh Capercaillie Buddy Guy Dream Apollo 8 Mary Jane Kelly Botulism Daylight saving time T